Netizen contribution
Recently, Ding Zhen won the lawsuit against black fans for infringement, and the defendant Wu was sentenced to compensate Ding Zhen Pearl for economic losses, mental damage and rights protection expenses totaling 61,000 yuan.
Then the defendant Wu posted on Baidu Tieba that he was unable to compensate, and he was completely unaware of the case. He even knew the verdict by looking at the hot search.

It is reported that in 2020, the "sweet wild boy" Ding Zhen became popular on the Internet. He signed a contract to become an employee of Litang County Cultural Tourism and Sports Investment Development Co., Ltd. and served as a local tourism ambassador.
Ding Zhen's popularity quickly became a hot topic on the Internet, and a large number of netizens deconstructed and created Ding Zhen on the Internet, including personal attacks, malicious photoshop, ridicule and even rumors.
On May 8, 2022, Ding Zhen posted a lawyer's statement on his official Weibo account "Litang Tourism Ambassador Ding Zhen Studio" stating that Beijing Guofeng Law Firm accepted Ding Zhen Pearl's commission and filed a lawsuit with the court regarding the infringement of its legal rights such as reputation rights by some Internet users.
